The Hindu (Client)
Software Engineer

Leading news/media publication house at Chennai wanted to upgrade their domino server. The customer's existing collaboration system was organized through a websphere portal with IBM lotus stack of products forming the core of the system. The customer had around 2000 Users and used IBM Lotus Domino for email, Sametime for instant Messaging and Quickplace for document sharing and collaboration. All of these were integrated using the WebSphere Portal and accessed on a single sign- on over a browser. Domino R5.0 was used along with Quickplace 3.0 version on a Windows platform. 
The customer had a requirement to upgrade this Portal to the latest versions of the relevant systems to improve employee productivity. The client wanted an entirely fresh setup of Domino instead of an upgrade as the existing setup deployed by another vendor was not to their satisfaction. Also, the Server is to be moved onto a new machine in a RHE Linux OS based platform.

Responsibilities:

    *  Responsible for upgrade for domino from R5 to 8.0.1 ; 
    *  Sametime version to 8.0
    *  Quickplace to Quickr 8.1 in multiple stages. ; 
    *  Integrated with WebSphere 6.1 with SSO using domino LDAP. ; 
    *  Http server was enabled to access the portal using browser. ; 
    *  Installation and configuration of new lotus domino mail setup. ; 
    *  Migrated the old data to the new setup and provided appropriate access. ; 
    *  Post implementation support.

Environment: Domino 8.0.1, WPS 6.1, Sametime 8.0, Quickr 8.1 & RHEL
